Reasoning: The paper deals with stereo matching using deep neural networks, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic interpretation and confidence maps, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions reducing over-fitting, which is a common problem in robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper was submitted to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition conference (CVPR), making cs.CVPR a possible sub-category as well.
